The paper proposes a framework for labeling entity alignments in knowledge graph datasets, which involves selecting informative instances for human labelers. This suggests a focus on machine learning and data management, which are covered by the sub-categories of cs.AI, cs.DB, and cs.LG. The paper also discusses the differences between labeling entity alignments and assigning class labels to single instances, which suggests a focus on natural language processing and information retrieval, covered by the sub-categories of cs.IR and cs.CL.
